        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Note that [P2P3Pa] is V2 times the distance from P3 to PzP4, which is maximized when P, lies on the midpoint of arc PaPa; similarly, [PaPsPo) is V2/2 times the distance from Ps to PaPo, which is maximized when Ps lies on the midpoint of arc P4P6. Thus the area of the octagon is maximized when Ps is the midpoint of arc P2P4 and Ps is the midpoint of arc PAP6. In this case, it is easy to calculate that (P2P3P4] = V5 - 1 and [P,PsP6) = V5/2 - 1, and so the area of the octagon is 3V5.",
